Preparations for Day of Sun Brisk All over World 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Preparations for grandly commemorating the Day of the Sun are being accelerated on the five continents.
 Inaugurated in more than 40 countries were preparatory committees with high-ranking government officials, heads of political parties and chiefs of friendly organizations as their chairmen including the deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace of Cambodia, the deputy speaker of the House of Representatives of Nepal, the chairman of the Supreme Council of the Socialist Party of Romania, the chairman of the Hungarian Workers' Party, the general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea, the secretary general of the National Executive Committee of the People's Party for the Reconstruction and the Democracy of Democratic Congo and the chairman of the Benin-Korea Amicable Association "Long Live Kim Jong Il, Supreme Leader". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committees are enhancing the atmosphere of commemorating the Day of the Sun by organizing colorful functions such as meetings, seminars on works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il, lectures, round-table talks, film shows and photo exhibitions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The noble ideological sentiments of the progressive people of the world hoping to convey through generations the immortal revolutionary life and exploits of the President, longing for him intensely, are erupting furiously on the threshold of April 15 to significantly glorify the Day of the Sun this year as a red-letter day common to all the people of the world.

U.S. Dangerous Attempt to Launch Nuclear War Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The U.S. hard-line conservative forces are pushing for the change of the present nuclear weapon system and the possession of nukes causing less additional destruction under the pretext of "threat" of the DPRK and other countries "to the U.S. security."
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says: This call of the U.S. bellicose forces is, in essence, aimed to make a nuclear war against other countries an established fact and step up its preparations for this war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is nothing but a brigandish logic intended to contain other countries with nukes and bring them under its control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those countries which the Bush group termed "dangerous states", "rogue states" are anti-imperialist independent countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "proliferation security initiative" touted by the Bush group only brings to light the arbitrary motive of the nuclear warmongers to deter other countries from having military deterrents for self-defence and dominate the world with nukes as they please. The U.S. is putting military pressure upon the DPRK and amassing armed forces for war in and around south Korea under the pretext of the "nuclear and missile threat" from the DPRK, escalating the tensions on the Korean peninsula. This is aimed at igniting a nuclear war on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' moves for a nuclear war which have become more reckless as the days go by only harden the resolution and will of the army and people of the DPRK to bolster the physical deterrent force to defend the sovereignty of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. option for a nuclear war would only precipitate its own self-destruction.

Premiere Given by Foreign Acrobats 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Foreign acrobats participating in the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival gave their premiere before a full house at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre Sunday evening.
 It was appreciated by working people and artistes in the city and foreign visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on stage colorful and peculiar acrobatic numbers they had prepared with all sincerity with deepest reverence for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The premiere began with The Level Swing performed by Russian acrobats which had carried away top prize from the International Acrobatic Festival held in Saratov, Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mongolian acrobats presented Trio Woman Plastic Etude which had been awarded gold, silver and bronze prizes in different international acrobatic festivals. They left deep impressions on the audience with their beautiful rhythm and harmonious and graceful plastic depiction to the melody of the Korean song "Kimjongilia." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A Swedish acrobat in Monocycle Stunts showed diverse tricks on monocycles of different types. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A Finnish acrobat who had won popularity in earlier spring festivals of the Day of the Sun presented Hand Tricks fascinating the spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roaring laughter burst when Mongolian acrobats presented a comic interlude Ball Kicking full of joy and optimism of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Other numbers included Mixed Twin Plastic Etude by Russians and Pole Stunt by Mongolians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance continues.

S. Koreans Urged to Judge Conservative Forces in Voting
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The pro-U.S. conservative forces such as the Grand National Party and the Democratic Party staged a political rebellion in the form of "impeachment against the president" against the will of the south Koreans. Finding themselves isolated, completely losing popularity, they are now running about like a headless chicken to lift the rate of support to them which has fallen on the ground.
 Commenting on this, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun today says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Koreans should eliminate on the political scene the ultra-right conservative forces in the upcoming "National Assembly election" and, by giving all the votes to the progressive reformist forces, make it an occasion for bringing the much awaited political reform and new politics. 
 The GNP is the main target of the fighting in the election. To expect "a fresh start" from this party is an illusion that does so harm but not any good. There is nothing more to expect from this party. What remains to be done is to bring down this traitorous party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The coming "National Assembly election" in south Korea is the capital chance to make a dramatic progress in the struggle for social justice and new life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation is opportune. It is time the south Koreans made a bold decision. The voters, men and women, young and old, should all participate in the election and sternly judge the remnants of the ultra-right conservative forces. The ballots should be cast for the progressive reformist forces at all the polling booths to bring about a complete change in south Korean politics.

Premiere of 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Premieres of the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival took place at theatres in Pyongyang�@Sunday.
 Performances were given at the Mansudae Art Theater, the Ponghwa Art Theatre, the Pyongyang Grand Theatre, the Pyongyang�@International Cinema House, the Moranbong Theatre, the Yun I Sang Concert Hall, the Central Youth Hall and the Central Workers Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were appreciated by Pyongyangites from all walks of life in the city, diplomatic envoys of different countries and staff�@members of foreign embassies here, foreign guests and overseas Koreans.�@&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese State Symphony Orchestra solemnly played the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Jong Il" presented by the orchestra stirred up the ardent reverence for�@leader Kim Jong Il in the theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mitsuko Okasawara, member of an art troupe of the Japan-Korea Musical and Artistic Interchange Society, sang with clear and sweet�@voice the song "Longing to See Pyongyang" and "Let's Sing of Pyongyang Tomorrow" created by herself. 
 Alexandr Grishekina, female singer of the Russian troupe of famous singers who is winner of international concours, presented "Song�@Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il", a singer of the State Opera Ballet Troupe who is heading the Mongolian art troupe "General on a�@Galloping White Horse",  British singer Suzanna Clarke who is winner of international concours the "Flower Lagoon," song of Pok Sun�@from the revolutionary opera "Tell the Story, Forest," and artistes from Cuba, Cambodia, Armenia, Bulgaria, Uzbekistan and many�@other countries successfully presented  other Korean songs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian Ballet Troupe performed ballets based on music by Tchaikovsky with refined rhythms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A singer from Spain who has participated in the festival several times sang "Song of Peace and Freedom" and "Starlight" which she�@wrote and composed representing her desire to venerate forever President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il as great men in the era of�@independence, pleasing the Korean people. Artistes of Indian, Egyptian and Ukrainian dance troupes, the Japanese Ito dance troupe,�@the Indonesian art troupe and other foreign troupes put on stages dances spiced with strong national flavor reflecting the�@optimistic life of their peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Belorussian music troupe and the Vietnamese art troupe and those from Georgia, Belgium, Argentine and Spain�@successfully staged world famous songs and songs reflecting the peculiar sentiment and optimistic life of their nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russian and American musicians displayed their high artistry and refined rendition in their presentations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Performances given by overseas Korean artistes were acclaimed by the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean artistes in Japan put on the stage mixed chorus "Let's Perform Songs and Dances on April Festival Stages", vocal solo by�@Merited Artiste Ri Yong Su "I Will Not Abandon My Faith," solo dance "Protecting Our Long Skirt and Jogori" by Song Yong Suk who is�@winner of February 16 Art Prize and other numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean artistes in China successfully represented "Cantata to Marshal Kim Il Sung" and songs "We Live Looking Up to Mt. Paektu" and�@" Spring of April Has Come" created by them through mixed chorus and female solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Jun Mu, head of the art troupe of Koreans in the U.S., enthusiastically conducted the Fourth Movement "We Swear" from the�@symphony "Our Leader Will Always Be with Us." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the art troupe of the International United Confederation of Koreans presented well the dance "Yangsando".�@&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their premieres the performers represented with high artistry the desire of the world people to hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem�@forever and the unbounded thanks and reverence for Kim Jong Il who made the revolutionary history of the President last forever in�@this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performances continue.

DPRK-New Zealand Friendship School Designated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang June 9 Taesong Middle School No. 1 was designated as DPRK-New Zealand Friendship School�@with due ceremony today.
 Present there on invitation were Don Borrie, chairman of the New Zealand-DPRK Society, and its secretary on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice-Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Jon Yong Jin who is chairman�@of the DPRK-New Zealand Friendship Association and other officials concerned, teachers and students of this school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory speeches were made by the two chairmen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony its participants talked to one another about the need to boost the friendly relations between the two�@countries and enjoyed an art performance given by students.

Chief of NDFSK Pyongyang Mission Calls for Struggle for National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) - The members of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) and the people of all strata in�@south Korea will wage a vigorous struggle to carry out the last instruction of President Kim Il Sung for national reunification and�@make redoubled efforts to implement the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration, a milestone of national reunification, holding leader�@Kim Jong Il in high esteem as the lodestar of national reunification, declared Jo Il Min, chief of the Pyongyang mission of the�@NDFSK, when  interviewed by KCNA today on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 He said that the reverence of the people in the south for�@Kim Il Sung, the eternal sun of the nation, is growing ever deeper as the Day of the Sun is drawing nearer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The higher the anger and disappointment of the people to the domination of the U.S. imperialists and the separatist and unpopular�@policy of the successive pro-American and flunkeyist ruling quarters mount in south Korea, the deeper their veneration for�@Kim Il Sung gets and the stronger their desire to hold�@Kim Jong Il in high esteem as the leader of the nation grows, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recalled that NDFSK and many patriotic organizations in south Korea are conducting diverse activities commemorating the Day of�@the Sun in April such as a lecture commemorating the day, reading session on the President's reminiscences, recitation of aphorisms�@of Kim Jong Il, inaugural meeting of the group for the study of the Songun policy, public presentation of this policy and the issue�@of national reunification, show of films and songs from the north after having celebrations of the great February holiday.

Youth Take Oath
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the young vanguard to uphold leader Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary leadership with�@loyalty true to the last instructions of President Kim Il Sung was held at the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace today with at�@least 50,000 youth and students attending.
 Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, made a report at the meeting,�@which was followed by speeches of others.�@ &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that it was an earnest request Kim Il Sung made to the Korean youth and students, the supreme requirement of the Korean�@revolution and a sure guarantee for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche and building a great prosperous powerful nation�@to uphold Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary leadership with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the youth and students would cherish the validity and the tremendous vitality of the Songun idea and politics of�@the Workers' Party of Korea as an unshakable faith, always work and live as required by them and ardently follow the Songun idea and�@firmly defend and thoroughly implement the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They underscored the need for all of them to consolidate the single-hearted unity of the revolutionary ranks as firm as an iron�@wall with transparent class awareness and the spirit of anti-imperialist struggle, actively join the People's Army and prepare�@themselves as one-match-for-a hundred soldiers and thus demonstrate the stamina of the Korean youth in the Songun era in the�@confrontation with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the youth and students will actively volunteer to work in difficult and labour consuming fields to dedicate their wisdom and�@enthusiasm, acquire rich scientific knowledge and technology as required by the IT age and steadily perform fresh miracles and�@exploits, true to the WPK's line of economic construction in the Songun era and thus contribute to accelerating the building of a�@great prosperous powerful nation, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was attended by Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, and others.

Statue of Kim Il Sung Erected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A statue of President Kim Il Sung was erected at the Mansudae Art Studio on the occasion of the Day�@of the Sun.
 The statue depicts Kim Il Sung on a military horse with a pair of binoculars in his hand.
 An unveiling ceremony was held today.�@&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, Jong Ha Chol, Kim Jung�@Rin and Kim Ki Nam, secretaries of the Central Committee of the WPK, and Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the statue was slowly unveiled by senior officials and persons of distinguished service, the statue standing imposingly there�@shed bright rays. That moment the participants broke into stormy cheers of "Hurrah!" and thousands of balloons soared into the sky. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket sent by Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the WPK, chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and�@supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, was laid before the statue amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then placed there were floral baskets in the name of the Central Committee of the WPK, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's�@Assembly, the DPRK Cabinet, working people's organizations, the ministries and the national institutions and organs, industrial�@establishments and universities in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the participants paid high tribute to Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam in a speech made at the ceremony said that the erection of the statue depicting the President on the military horse,�@the first of its kind in the country, as a great monument representing loyalty in the Songun era brought high honor and joy to all�@servicepersons of the KPA and people including the officials and employees of the Mansudae Art Studio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statue will tower high as one more monument in the Songun era representing loyalty thanks to the wise leadership of Kim�@Jong Il and the intense fidelity of the Party members and other working people throughout the country including the officials and�@creators of the Studio.

7th Aesthetic Symposium on Present Times and National Art Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The 7th Aesthetic Symposium on the Present Times and National Art took place here today.
 It was attended by delegations and delegates from Russia, China and Egypt and a delegation of Koreans in China staying here to�@participate in the symposium, a DPRK delegation, heads and members of cultural delegations and art troupes and overseas Korean�@artistes participating in the 22nd April Spring Friendship Art Festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Jong Ho, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of the Unions of Literature and the�@Arts of Korea who is chairman of the organizing committee of the festival, Song Sok Hwan, vice-chairman of the organizing committee,�@and other officials concerned and researchers, creators and artistes in the field of culture and art in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Ho, made a report titled "Let's keep national art in full bloom to glorify the history and tradition of the nation" at the�@symposium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that only by developing national culture and art is it possible to foil the vicious and crafty policy of the imperialists�@to obliterate national culture and protect the soul of the nation from their ideological and cultural poisoning and glorify its�@history and tradition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brilliant efflorescence of the Songun revolutionary literature and art in the DPRK under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il�@clearly proves that it is a true way of glorifying the history and tradition of the nation to develop its art independently, he�@said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all the participants to creditably play a pace-setter's role in developing the national art independently and pool�@efforts and wisdom for the prosperity and development of the country and the nation in the idea of independence, peace and�@friendship in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to speeches, a congratulatory message sent to the symposium by the minister of Culture and Tourism of Indonesia was read out�@by its Vice-Minister Thamrin B. Bachri who is heading the Indonesian government cultural delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A Russian delegate, the head of a Chinese delegation, Chairperson Mitsuko Ogasawara of the Japan-Korea Musical and Artistic�@Interchange Society, an Egyptian delegate, and delegate of the DPRK Pak Hyong Sop, director of the Korean National Music and Dance�@Institute, made speeches under the respective titles "April Spring Friendship Art Festival is an international art festival most�@famous in our planet," "An elementary view on the development of the world's national art in the present times," "Korean songs�@truthfully represent the people's noble feelings and their life which are of social significance", "Science and beauty" and "On�@successfully preserving the Juche character and national identity in music by actively encouraging folk songs in the DPRK".�@&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers stressed the need to develop the national art on a new basis and, at the same time, introduce achievements made by�@other national art and register successes in developing beautiful art by the creative efforts of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They also underscored the need to actively develop the popular art based on the Juche character and national identity as required by�@the times.
